      • getLogSubType

        public Integer getLogSubType()
        In most cases the log type is sufficient to determine how to classify a log item, but in some cases further granularity is required. One such example is deletion/undeletion, which are both part of the "deletion" log type.

      • setLogSubType

        public void setLogSubType(Integer logSubType)
        In most cases the log type is sufficient to determine how to classify a log item, but in some cases further granularity is required. One such example is deletion/undeletion, which are both part of the "deletion" log type.
